    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "If you write a `when` wrong the resulting error message doesn't say where the when came from\r\n`@when('@:0.87,@0.99:')`:\r\n```\r\n==> Error: Invalid version specifier\r\n['hydrogen', '@:0.87,@0.99:']\r\n         ^\r\n```\r\nor\r\n`@when(':0.87')`:\r\n```\r\n==> Error: Unexpected token\r\n['hydrogen', ':0.87']\r\n          ^\r\n```\r\nThese are easy enough to look for, but if the error is in a `depends_on` or a `conflicts` `when=`, tracking down the failing `when` is more difficult.",
